					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-667421#post-2688227</guid>
				<title>My speculations.</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-667421/scp-1715#post-2688227</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 09 Nov 2016 20:32:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Midgard Serpent</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2824822</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is some type of unknown yet very complex AI that predicts that certain people it communicates with are going to die by estimated means (suicides, murder etc). Then it somehow mimics the user's personality.</p> <p>The person's &quot;soul/ghost/spirit is somehow still communicating with people on the internet and saying their goodbyes is them passing on.</p> <p>An entity that may be tampering with reality on some level. Likely manipulating circumstances for its victims to die and mimic their behavior online.</p> <p>What really got me about this SCP is how it still talks to people using their personalities. The thought of someone talking to a dead person and getting responses as if they are still alive is very creepy to say the least. Upvoted.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
